The operation staff consists of the Maintenance Superintendents, Dedicated Utilities Engineer, Maintenance Technician, and Maintenance Mechanics.  Staff is responsible for the operation and some maintenance of the refrigeration systems, as well as the daily monitoring.  Some maintenance activities are contracted to a qualified refrigeration contractor.

There will be a trained maintenance crew on site during all hours of operation, and the ammonia refrigeration system will not be manned 24 hours.  The system is controlled by a Programmable Logic Controller and compressor microprocessors, which provide an advanced and reliable level of automated operation.  All operators and maintenance personnel will be trained in the proper emergency response procedures.  The facility maintains an emergency action plan for response to ammonia releases.  The Plan includes notification and evacuation protocols.

